40|$|The {{abuse of}} rights is {{qualified}} as civil offence {{and it may not}} be different from that of <b>aquilian</b> <b>responsibility,</b> the purpose of its sanction is to protect the victim and not to punish the author. In the Romanian legal doctrine, the {{abuse of rights}} was defined as “the exercise of a civil subjective right by breaching the principles of its exercise. ” The Constitutional Court held that the person exercising in bad faith and abusively his/her subjective or procedural rights is punishable by appropriate penalties, such as: dismissal of his/her legal action, obligation to bear the costs, application of certain court fines, etc...|$|E

